<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First off, I got a question about the average cost of items on other servers. On Xegony, a Sarnak Battle shield goes for 25-30k. I personally think this is NUTS. Is that normal for other servers?<P>Now, I have been hovering around 190wis for awhile now, and have a general plan,, but was hoping for some input on things I may have overlooked.<P>I traded 2 Platinum Diamond rings for something called a Kunzar Kujuch (I think that was a good deal, but not sure), then traded that for a Paw of Opella. Dik has a dolly now. I traded my Dark Ember to a guildmate for his Springwood Club, just so I can have something to bash with sometimes. That put me at 194wis. <P>I, 2 days ago, then went to Sebilis, and got into a group that decided to go to the Pickler. First drop was a Donal's Helm. I swapped out my Runed Circlet for the helm and gained 18AC. Back down to 190wis. Then I got a Clay Guardian shield. Nice shield. I am keeping it for a bit (I'll explain later).<P>Last night, got into another group and we hit the Pickler again. This time I got a Donal's Bracer. Swapped out my EM bracer for it, lost 20mana, picked up 15AC. Still at 190wis.<P>Now, my plan: I am going to Hate again this saturday. I am hoping for EM legs or BP. If I get either, that will put me at 199wis. (BP is 9wis more than the Sebilite Scale coat I have now). I can then afford to drop my CGS for the Clay Guardian Shield. I will remain at 190wis and pick up even more AC.<P>Now, my question: Is there something I may have overlooked in my plan? I want to keep around 190-200wis, and I am trying to increase my AC as much as possible. I do not have 25k+ to put into any UBER items.<P>I have:<BR>Donal's Helm<BR>Velium Ruby Viel<BR>2 Forrest Loops<BR>Crysoberyl Talisman<BR>Sebilite Scale Coat<BR>Adamantite Epoletes<BR>Donal's Arms<BR>Donal's Bracer<BR>Supple Scale Armband (<--why is it called an armband if it goes on your wrist?)<BR>Gauntlets of the Black<BR>2 Velium Jasper Rings<BR>Girdle of the Diligent<BR>Ry'gorr Chain Leggings<BR>Donal's Boots<BR>Medicine Totem<P>I guess my legs are the easiest to upgrade, providing I don't get EM legs in Hate this weekend. I have about 4500 cash to work with, and can maybe come up with another 2500-3k if I have to. As it stands, I have 920AC with all self buffs (Armor of Protection, Shield of Words, Heroic Bond).<p>[This message has been edited by Dikmer (edited 04-25-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RZaddict</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Try to upgrade your talisman to a Bone Amulet of Blade Turning. It drops in Karnors, has 2 ac, 6 wis, and 5 charges of guard, the 29 AC spell. The 5 charges are good in certain situations. Plus the 6 wis is very nice. And the name is cool as hell :P<P>------------------<BR>RZaddict<BR>Addicted to PVP</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What about:<P>Crysoberyl Talisman  replaced with Goblin Soul Caller from FM (+5 Wis +10 vsMg)  Cost: 1k possibly 2k.<P>Ry'gorr Chain Leggings  replaced with Jarsath Scale Leggings from Karnors (+15 AC +5 Wis +5 Int) Cost: Free, just find the Undead Jailor.<P>Just to up both AC and Wiz?<P><BR><P>------------------<BR>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara<BR>50th Cleric of Tunare<BR>~Calizana Rhinelander<BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR><A HREF="http://www.lostorder.com" TARGET=_blank>Lost Order of Akalabeth</A><BR>Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="